    h3 Feature Extraction
    p.text-content In our system we used Mel-frequency Cepstrum Coefficients (MFCC) as our main features.
    ul
      li.text-content we detect each note of the whole file. we achieve this by using the librosa in python.
      li.text-content we choose 10 frames from the beginning of each note and compute a 13-dimensional MFCC feature from each frames. Since the sample rate is 44100, the hop-size is 1024, and the window-size is 2048. There will be 50 percent overlap of each chosen frame.
      li.text-content After unrolling the MFCC feature of each note and normalization, we develop our feature matrix, of which every sample has 130 dimensions. We choose data from five instruments: violin, guitar, piano, flute, and sax.
      li.text-content We also computed first and second derivatives of MFCCs, of which the feature dimension for one note would be 260 and 390
