    h3 Feature Optimization
    p.text-content Since we intend to make it a real-time system, thus we must take the running time of our algorithm into our consideration. The original MFCC feature we extracted is of quite high dimensions, which will definitely increase the computations comparing to lower dimensional features. That's why we used PCA to reduce the dimension and optimize our features. We tried the dimension of 130, 50 and 20 to do the data optimization.
    p.text-content In following Figure we show the eigen-values of features matrix, which are exactly corresponding to the weights of each dimension of features after PCA analysis. As we can see, the first some dimensions already centralizes most of the weights. According to the experiments we finally choose 50 dimensional features in our system.
